<div class="prose-content max-w-3xl">

  <p>Like many GP practices, we use a telephone triage system to make sure every patient gets seen by the right person, as quickly as possible.</p>

  <h2>When you call us</h2>
  <p>When you call the surgery, our reception team will ask you a few brief questions about what you need help with. This helps us:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Make sure you see the right clinician for your needs</li>
    <li>Offer you an appointment at the most appropriate time</li>
    <li>Suggest a faster alternative if one is available (such as Pharmacy First)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Our reception team are not medically trained, but they follow NHS guidelines for directing calls appropriately. They are not able to give clinical advice.</p>

  <h2>Types of clinician</h2>
  <p>Depending on what you need, you may be offered an appointment with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GP</strong> — for complex or ongoing health concerns</li>
    <li><strong>Advanced Nurse Practitioner (ANP)</strong> — for many common conditions, minor illness, and health reviews</li>
    <li><strong>Practice Nurse</strong> — for wound care, immunisations, chronic disease management, and health checks</li>
    <li><strong>Practice Pharmacist</strong> — for medication queries and some clinical reviews</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Telephone and face-to-face appointments</h2>
  <p>Many concerns can be dealt with quickly and effectively over the phone. We'll offer you a telephone appointment in the first instance for many routine queries. If a face-to-face examination is needed, we'll arrange this.</p>

  <h2>Waiting times</h2>
  <p>We aim to offer urgent on-the-day appointments to patients with clinically urgent needs. Routine appointments are offered as quickly as possible, usually within a few days.</p>
  <p>If you are waiting for a routine appointment and your condition changes or worsens, please call us again so we can reassess your priority.</p>

  <h2>Birthday Month Review (BMR)</h2>
  <p>Each year, patients with long-term conditions receive a Birthday Month Review — a structured annual review that takes place in the month of your birthday. You'll be invited to attend by letter or text.</p>
  <p>The review gives you and your clinician the chance to check how your condition is being managed, review your medications, and set goals for the coming year. Please try to attend when invited, as these reviews help us provide proactive care and avoid complications.</p>

  <h2>Clinical services we provide</h2>
  <p>In addition to routine GP and nurse appointments, our practice provides a range of specialist clinics and services:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Child Health Surveillance</strong> — developmental checks and reviews for children</li>
    <li><strong>Contraceptive Services</strong> — including contraceptive counselling, pill prescribing, and fitting/removal of implants and coils (IUCD/IUS)</li>
    <li><strong>Minor Surgery</strong> — including skin lesion removal and joint injections</li>
    <li><strong>INR / Warfarin Monitoring</strong> — regular blood tests and dose management for anticoagulated patients</li>
    <li><strong>Long-term Condition (LTC) Clinics</strong> — specialist nurse clinics for asthma, COPD, diabetes, hypertension, and other chronic conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Alternatives to GP appointments</h2>
  <p>Many conditions don't need a GP at all. Please consider:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/get-help/pharmacy-first/">Pharmacy First</a> — for UTIs, skin infections, earache, sore throat, and more</li>
    <li><a href="/get-help/self-referral/">Self-referral services</a> — direct access to physio, mental health, and other NHS services</li>
    <li><a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/" rel="noopener noreferrer">NHS Inform</a> — trusted health information and self-care advice</li>
  </ul>

</div>
